name: ITLibArtworkFormat
desc: These constants specify the possible formats of the data that imageDataFormat returns.

items.name: case none
items.desc: The image data format is unknown.

items.name: case bitmap
items.desc: The image data corresponds to a bitmap image.

items.name: case JPEG
items.desc: The image data corresponds to a JPEG image.

items.name: case JPEG2000
items.desc: The image data corresponds to a JPEG2000 image.

items.name: case GIF
items.desc: The image data corresponds to a GIF image.

items.name: case PNG
items.desc: The image data corresponds to a PNG image.

items.name: case BMP
items.desc: The image data corresponds to a bitmap image.

items.name: case TIFF
items.desc: The image data corresponds to a TIFF image.

items.name: case PICT
items.desc: The image data corresponds to a PICT image.
